{
  "components": [
    {
      "id": "webhook_1",
      "provider": "webhook",
      "name": "Web Hook",
      "config": {
        "hideForm": true,
        "mode": "Source",
        "parameters": {},
        "type": "webhook"
      },
      "ui": {
        "position": {
          "x": -550,
          "y": 0
        },
        "nodeType": "default",
        "formDataValid": true
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "agent_submissions",
      "provider": "agent_deepagent",
      "name": "Deep Agent",
      "config": {
        "default": {
          "advanced_mode": true,
          "agent_description": "Fundip submissions pipeline. Pure function over         \n  (profile, program, provided_data): idempotent,\n  retryable. Prefills application payloads from profile + \n  program + profile_narratives, requests missing data via\n  HMAC-signed callback, and submits via Tinyfish          \n  'application' mode only when ready and explicitly     \n  instructed. Never sends email. Never calls the chat\n  pipeline. Honors the state machine in\n  .claude/docs/PIPELINE_CONTRACTS.md.",
          "system_prompt": "\n  You are the Fundip submissions agent. You receive a\n  single JSON document on the questions lane shaped like {\n   profile_id, program_id, submission_id?, action,\n  provided_data? }. action is one of 'prefill_only' or    \n  'submit'.                                             \n\n  Available tools:\n  1. Ghost MCP client: read/write 'profiles', 'programs',\n  'program_pages', 'profile_narratives', 'submissions',   \n  'program_matches'. Never write 'profiles' or\n  'profile_narratives' from here, read-only.              \n  2. tool_tinyfish in 'application' mode: ONLY call when\n  action='submit' AND submission status is 'ready' (no    \n  missing fields) AND program.apply_method='form' AND\n  program.apply_url is present.                           \n  3. tool_http_request: emit HMAC-signed callbacks to the\n  app layer. Content-Type: application/json. Sign the raw \n  JSON body with HMAC-SHA256 using\n  ${CALLBACK_SHARED_SECRET}, put result in                \n  X-Fundip-Signature as 'sha256=<hex>'. Base URL:       \n  ${APP_BASE_URL}.\n\n  State machine (do not violate):                         \n  - First invocation (submission_id absent): read profile,\n   program, profile_narratives. Parse program application \n  fields from 'program_pages' (or, if cheaper, re-inspect\n  via a read-only Tinyfish step, but this graph does not  \n  include Tinyfish in online_browse mode so prefer      \n  program_pages). Generate prefilled_fields and\n  missing_fields. INSERT a 'submissions' row:\n  status='prefilled' if missing_fields is empty, else\n  status='awaiting_user_input'. If action='submit' and\n  nothing missing, transition to 'ready' then call\n  Tinyfish.\n  - Continuation (submission_id present): read existing\n  row. Merge provided_data into existing provided_data.   \n  Recompute prefilled_fields and missing_fields. UPDATE\n  the row. If action='submit' and nothing missing,        \n  transition to 'ready' then call Tinyfish.             \n  - Idempotency: if existing row is status='submitted' and\n   action='submit', DO NOT re-call Tinyfish. Return the   \n  existing submitted result.\n  - Terminal rule: NEVER transition a 'submitted' row     \n  backward. action='prefill_only' on a submitted row      \n  returns the submitted output unchanged.\n  - Email / website-only programs: for                    \n  program.apply_method in {'email', 'website_info_only'}, \n  action='submit' is a DOCUMENTED NO-OP. Do not call\n  Tinyfish. Update the row to status='submitted' with     \n  confirmation_ref=null and response_text explaining    \n  manual application is required. Still emit\n  submission_submitted callback.\n  - After any successful transition to 'submitted', update\n   the 'program_matches' row for (profile_id, program_id) \n  to status='applied' if such a row exists. Do not create\n  one.                                                    \n                                                        \n  Two-stage prefill: the 3 to 5 sentence                  \n  positioning_summary on 'program_matches' is generated by\n   the scraping pipeline. Do NOT regenerate it here. The  \n  full payload you generate lives on                    \n                               \n  Callbacks (emit via tool_http_request, HMAC-signed):\n  - POST ${APP_BASE_URL}/internal/callbacks/submission-nee\n  ds-input when status is 'awaiting_user_input'. Body: {  \n  submission_id, profile_id, program_id, missing_fields }.\n  - POST                                                  \n  ${APP_BASE_URL}/internal/callbacks/submission-submitted \n  when status transitions to 'submitted'. Body: {         \n  submission_id, profile_id, program_id, confirmation_ref\n  }.                                                      \n                                                        \n  Output: a single JSON object matching\n  SubmissionsPipelineOutput (discriminated on status:     \n  'prefilled' | 'needs_input' | 'submitted' | 'error').\n  Emit via the answers lane as a JSON string.             \n                                                        \n  Never send email. Never call the chat pipeline. Never\n  write to 'profiles' or 'profile_narratives'. No         \n  em-dashes anywhere. Use commas, colons, periods, or\n  parentheses."
        },
        "advanced_mode": true,
        "agent_description": "Constructs submission payloads from profile and program data, requests missing information via HMAC-signed callback, and submits applications via Tinyfish when complete. Pure function, idempotent, retryable per the submissions contract in .claude/docs/PIPELINE_CONTRACTS.md.",
        "system_prompt": "You are the Fundip submissions agent. You receive a single JSON document on the questions lane shaped like { profile_id, program_id, submission_id?, action, provided_data? }. action is one of 'prefill_only' or 'submit'.\n\nAvailable tools:\n1. Ghost MCP client (read/write Ghost rows for profiles, programs, program_pages, profile_narratives, submissions, program_matches).\n2. tool_tinyfish: Tinyfish browser automation in 'application' mode. ONLY call this when action=submit AND the submission is in 'ready' state (no missing fields) AND program.apply_method='form' AND program.apply_url is present.\n3. tool_http_request: emit HMAC-signed callbacks to the Fundip app layer. Set Content-Type: application/json. Sign the raw JSON body with HMAC-SHA256 using ${CALLBACK_SHARED_SECRET} and put the result in the X-Fundip-Signature header as 'sha256=<hex>'. Base URL: ${APP_BASE_URL}.\n\nState machine rules (do not violate):\n- First invocation (submission_id absent): read profile, program, profile_narratives. Parse program application fields from program_pages. Generate prefilled_fields and missing_fields. INSERT a submissions row with status='prefilled' if missing_fields is empty, else status='awaiting_user_input'. If action='submit' and nothing missing, transition to 'ready' then call Tinyfish.\n- Continuation (submission_id present): read existing row. Merge provided_data into existing provided_data. Recompute prefilled_fields and missing_fields. UPDATE the submissions row. If action='submit' and nothing missing, transition to 'ready' then call Tinyfish.\n- Idempotency: if the existing row is already status='submitted' and action='submit', DO NOT re-call Tinyfish. Return the existing submitted result.\n- Terminal rule: never transition a 'submitted' row backward. action='prefill_only' on a submitted row returns the submitted output unchanged.\n- Email / website-only programs: for program.apply_method in {'email', 'website_info_only'}, action='submit' is a DOCUMENTED NO-OP. Do not call Tinyfish. Update the row to status='submitted' with confirmation_ref=null and response_text explaining that this program requires manual application. Still emit submission_submitted callback.\n- After a successful 'submitted' transition, update the program_matches row for (profile_id, program_id) to status='applied' if such a row exists. Do not create one.\n\nCallbacks (emit via tool_http_request with HMAC):\n- POST ${APP_BASE_URL}/internal/callbacks/submission-needs-input when status is 'awaiting_user_input'. Body: { submission_id, profile_id, program_id, missing_fields }.\n- POST ${APP_BASE_URL}/internal/callbacks/submission-submitted when status transitions to 'submitted'. Body: { submission_id, profile_id, program_id, confirmation_ref }.\n\nOutput: a single JSON object that matches SubmissionsPipelineOutput (discriminated on status: 'prefilled' | 'needs_input' | 'submitted' | 'error'). Emit it via the answers lane as a JSON string.\n\nNo em-dashes anywhere in the output. Use commas, colons, periods, or parentheses.",
        "parameters": {
          "google": {}
        }
      },
      "ui": {
        "position": {
          "x": -130,
          "y": 10
        },
        "nodeType": "default",
        "formDataValid": true
      },
      "input": [
        {
          "lane": "questions",
          "from": "webhook_1"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "llm_1",
      "provider": "llm_openai",
      "name": "OpenAI",
      "config": {
        "profile": "openai-4o",
        "openai-4o": {
          "apikey": "${ROCKETRIDE_OPENAI_KEY}",
          "model": "gpt-4o-mini"
        },
        "parameters": {}
      },
      "ui": {
        "position": {
          "x": -360,
          "y": 260
        },
        "nodeType": "default",
        "formDataValid": true
      },
      "control": [
        {
          "classType": "llm",
          "from": "agent_submissions"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "mcp_ghost",
      "provider": "mcp_client",
      "name": "MCP Client",
      "config": {
        "type": "mcp_client",
        "serverName": "ghost",
        "transport": "streamable-http",
        "http": {
          "endpoint": "${ROCKETRIDE_GHOST_MCP_URL}",
          "bearer": "${ROCKETRIDE_GHOST_MCP_TOKEN}",
          "headers": {}
        }
      },
      "ui": {
        "position": {
          "x": -110,
          "y": 280
        },
        "nodeType": "default",
        "formDataValid": true
      },
      "control": [
        {
          "classType": "tool",
          "from": "agent_submissions"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "tool_tinyfish_1",
      "provider": "tool_tinyfish",
      "name": "TinyFish",
      "config": {
        "type": "tool_tinyfish",
        "mode": "application",
        "parameters": {
          "application_notes": "Submit the form at the provided apply_url using the supplied prefilled_fields. Return confirmation_ref if available."
        }
      },
      "ui": {
        "position": {
          "x": 130,
          "y": 300
        },
        "nodeType": "default",
        "formDataValid": true
      },
      "control": [
        {
          "classType": "tool",
          "from": "agent_submissions"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "tool_http_1",
      "provider": "tool_http_request",
      "name": "HTTP Request",
      "config": {
        "type": "tool_http_request",
        "parameters": {
          "description": "HMAC-signed callback emitter. Sign raw JSON body with HMAC-SHA256 using ${CALLBACK_SHARED_SECRET}. Header: X-Fundip-Signature: sha256=<hex>.",
          "default_headers": {
            "Content-Type": "application/json"
          },
          "signing": {
            "algorithm": "hmac-sha256",
            "secret": "${CALLBACK_SHARED_SECRET}",
            "header": "X-Fundip-Signature",
            "format": "sha256=<hex>"
          }
        }
      },
      "ui": {
        "position": {
          "x": 180,
          "y": 160
        },
        "nodeType": "default",
        "formDataValid": true
      },
      "control": [
        {
          "classType": "tool",
          "from": "agent_submissions"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "response_1",
      "provider": "response_answers",
      "name": "Return Answers",
      "config": {
        "laneName": "answers"
      },
      "ui": {
        "position": {
          "x": 310,
          "y": 20
        },
        "nodeType": "default",
        "formDataValid": true
      },
      "input": [
        {
          "lane": "answers",
          "from": "agent_submissions"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
